## Execution Requirements

All test cases must be executed using Playwright MCP with the following requirements:
1. **Complete Coverage** - Run every test under all three categories:
   - Sanity Tests
   - Logic Tests 
   - Error Handling Tests
2. **Browser Support** - By default, tests should run only on Chrome/Chromium unless specifically requested to run on additional browsers:
   - Chromium (default)
   - Firefox (optional)
   - WebKit (optional)
3. **Parallel Execution** - Tests should run in parallel when possible to reduce execution time

## Test Report Generation

After executing the full test set, generate a comprehensive Test Report that includes:
- **Test ID** - Unique identifier matching the Test Plan
- **Test Name** - Name of the test from the Test Plan
- **Category** - One of: "Sanity", "Logic", or "Error Handling"
- **Status** - One of: "Passed", "Failed", or "Skipped"
- **Execution Time** - Duration in seconds
- **Error Message** - Detailed error message (if failed)
- **Screenshot/Trace** - Link to screenshot or trace file (if available)

## Output Format

The test results should be presented in two formats:

1. **Formatted Table** - For immediate review, display results as a formatted table:
```
Test ID | Test Name           | Category      | Status | Execution Time | Error Message
--------|--------------------|--------------|---------|-----------------|--------------
TS-001  | Verify Basic Login | Sanity       | Passed  | 1.25s          | -
LT-001  | Validate Rule X    | Logic        | Failed  | 2.34s          | Expected X but got Y
EH-001  | Test Invalid Input | Error Handling | Passed | 0.95s         | -
```

2. **CSV File** - Generate a CSV file with the same data:
```
Test ID,Test Name,Category,Status,Execution Time,Error Message,Screenshot/Trace
TS-001,Verify Basic Login,Sanity,Passed,1.25s,,https://example.com/screenshots/TS-001.png
LT-001,Validate Rule X,Logic,Failed,2.34s,Expected X but got Y,https://example.com/traces/LT-001.zip
EH-001,Test Invalid Input,Error Handling,Passed,0.95s,,
```

## CSV File Storage

- Save the test results CSV file in the "test-results" folder
- Use a descriptive filename that includes the target system/feature and date (e.g., "google_search_test_results_2023-11-15.csv")

## Implementation Guidelines

1. **Test Setup**:
   - Use standard Playwright test fixtures
   - Implement proper isolation between tests
   - Ensure tests can run independently

2. **Execution Configuration**:
   - Set appropriate timeouts for different test types
   - Configure retry logic for flaky tests
   - Enable video recording for failed tests

3. **Result Verification**:
   - Only include verified and accurate test results
   - No test implementation code in the report
   - Include links to artifacts (screenshots, videos, traces)

4. **Performance Monitoring**:
   - Track execution time for each test
   - Report total execution time for the test suite
   - Identify and flag slow-running tests

5. **Error Handling**:
   - Capture detailed error messages
   - Include stack traces where applicable
   - Take screenshots at the point of failure

6. **Report Summary**:
   - Include overall pass/fail statistics
   - Group results by test category
   - Highlight critical failures
   - Add timestamp of test execution

## Best Practices

1. **Pre-Execution Validation**:
   - Verify the test environment is properly set up
   - Confirm all dependencies are available
   - Check that the application under test is in the expected state

2. **Post-Execution Cleanup**:
   - **Browser Cleanup** - After completing all Playwright MCP test execution, explicitly close all used browser instances using the browser close function
   - Ensure all browser instances are closed
   - Remove temporary test data
   - Reset application state for future test runs

3. **CI/CD Integration**:
   - Configure tests to run in CI/CD pipelines
   - Archive test artifacts for later review
   - Set appropriate failure thresholds

4. **Resource Management**:
   - Optimize parallel execution to match available system resources
   - Implement proper handling of shared resources
   - Monitor memory usage during test execution
